<HL>
   Business Brief -- American Credit Optical Inc.:
   Firm to Buy Some Assets
   Of Allied Marketing Group
</HL>
<DATE>
09/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   ACOI
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
ADVERTISING, MARKETING, PUBLIC RELATIONS (ADV)
</IN>
<LP>
   American Credit Optical Inc. said it signed a definitive
agreement to purchase $20 million of the operating assets of
Dallas-based Allied Marketing Group Inc. The assets are
related primarily to closely held Allied's direct mail
marketing division.
   American Credit Optical, a Fort Worth, Texas, financial
concern, said the purchase is subject to financing, which
Dean Witter Reynolds Inc. has been engaged to arrange. The
company said it expects to complete the transaction within
the next several weeks.
</LP>
